!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

beautiful /ˈbjuːtɪfʊl/

1. ADJ A beautiful person is very attractive to look at. 美丽的 

例： She was a very beautiful woman. 她是个非常美丽的女人。 

2. ADJ If you describe something as beautiful , you mean that it is very attractive or pleasing. 迷人的 

例： New England is beautiful. 新英格兰很迷人。 

例： It was a beautiful morning. 那是个迷人的早晨。 

3. beautifully ADV 迷人地 

例： The children behaved beautifully. 孩子们表现甚佳。 

4. ADJ You can describe something that someone does as beautiful when they do it very skilfully. 出色的 

例： That's a beautiful shot! 那一射真漂亮！ 

5. beautifully ADV 出色地 

例： The Sixers played beautifully. 费城76人队打得很出色。

</div>

